Given your family's financial circumstances at the time, how were you and your brothers able to attend summer camp? A. That first summer, my oldest sister and her husband and her husband's family all pitched in to send us to camp. Q. And when you arrived at camp that summer, how long had it been since your father passed away? A. So the end of October '93, so what is that, nine months? Q. Did there come a time that summer at Interlochen Arts Camp when you met a man and a woman? A. Yes. Q. Where were you when that happened? A. I was in the main campus area where all the students hung out during a break and where all the little cafes were and sort of the gift shop. And I was on a park bench or a picnic bench with my friends from camp. And we were eating ice cream. Q. What do you remember happening next? A. Well, we were sitting around and socializing.
